Despite record numbers of COVID-19 cases in the U.S. from mid-June onward and an increasing percentage of positive test results, Trump continued to mostly downplay the pandemic, including his false claim in early July 2020 that 99 percent of COVID-19 cases are "totally harmless."[592][593] He also began insisting that all states should open schools to in-person education in the fall despite a July spike in reported cases.[594]
